name: Kukui Nut Lei
description:
In Hawaiʻi the kukui is a symbol of enlightenment, protection and peace. Originally reserved for royalty in ancient times, the kukui nut was worn by the reigning chiefs and Kings of Hawaii, known as Ali'I, during the days of the Hawaiian Monarchy. 
 
Kukui Nut Leis are perfect for both casual and formal ensembles.

*Made with highly polished natural Pacific kukui nuts and knotted brown satin ribbon.  
approx. 34"
